Note:
This file handles devirtualization optimization for MIR.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process virtual call analysis and concrete type detection
- Handle protocol/trait method resolution to concrete implementations
- Manage speculative devirtualization with guard insertion
- Process virtual call to direct call conversion

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Devirtualization eliminates indirect call overhead
- Proper devirtualization enables inlining of virtual methods
- Devirtualization significantly improves object-oriented code performance

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Type propagation for receiver type identification
- Single implementation detection for protocols
- Speculative devirtualization with type guards
- Virtual table bypass for known concrete types
:End Note

Note: ========== IMPORTS ==========
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir.runa" as MIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/cfg.runa" as CFG
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/ssa.runa" as SSA
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/dominance.runa" as Dominance
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

Note: ============================================================
Note: TYPE DEFINITIONS
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
DevirtualizationContext stores all state needed for devirtualization optimization.
It tracks type information for SSA values, maintains statistics about
devirtualized calls, and caches results for efficiency.

The context includes type propagation information and virtual call site data
to enable effective devirtualization analysis.

Size calculation (64-bit pointers, 8 bytes each):
- 13 fields * 8 bytes = 104 bytes per context
@End Reasoning

Type called "DevirtualizationContext":
    cfg as Integer                          Note: CFG pointer for current function
    ssa_ptr as Integer                      Note: SSA information pointer
    dominance_ptr as Integer                Note: Dominance tree pointer
    current_function_ptr as Integer         Note: Pointer to function being optimized
    devirtualized_calls as Integer          Note: Counter for devirtualized calls
    speculative_devirt as Integer           Note: Counter for speculative devirt
    total_virtual_calls as Integer          Note: Total virtual calls found
    virtual_call_sites as Integer           Note: List of VirtualCallSite structures
    type_info_map as Integer                Note: Dictionary: value_id -> TypePropagationInfo
    receiver_types as Integer               Note: Dictionary: call_site -> concrete_type
    blocks_processed as Integer             Note: Number of blocks analyzed
    single_impl_cache as Integer            Note: Dictionary: protocol_ptr -> impl_ptr
    guard_threshold as Integer              Note: Confidence threshold for guards (0-100)
End Type

@Reasoning
VirtualCallSite represents a single virtual call that may be devirtualized.
It captures all information needed to determine the concrete type of the
receiver and perform the devirtualization transformation.

We track the receiver value ID to query type information and determine
if we have a concrete type available.

Size calculation:
- 9 fields * 8 bytes = 72 bytes per virtual call site
@End Reasoning

Type called "VirtualCallSite":
    call_instruction_ptr as Integer         Note: Pointer to MIR_CALL_INDIRECT instruction
    call_block_ptr as Integer               Note: Pointer to containing basic block
    receiver_value_id as Integer            Note: SSA value ID of receiver object
    method_selector as Integer              Note: Method identifier (offset/name)
    protocol_ptr as Integer                 Note: Protocol/trait type
    concrete_type_ptr as Integer            Note: Known concrete type (if determined)
    confidence as Integer                   Note: Confidence level (0-100)
    can_devirtualize as Integer             Note: Boolean: 1 if eligible, 0 otherwise
    devirtualized as Integer                Note: Boolean: 1 if transformed, 0 otherwise
End Type

@Reasoning
TypePropagationInfo tracks the concrete type information for an SSA value.
Used during type propagation analysis to determine receiver types.

Confidence levels:
- 0-25: Unknown/weak
- 26-50: Likely (from heuristics)
- 51-75: Probable (from casts)
- 76-100: Certain (from allocation)

Size calculation:
- 6 fields * 8 bytes = 48 bytes per type info
@End Reasoning

Type called "TypePropagationInfo":
    value_id as Integer                     Note: SSA value ID being tracked
    concrete_type_ptr as Integer            Note: Pointer to concrete type
    confidence as Integer                   Note: Confidence level (0-100)
    source_instruction as Integer           Note: Instruction that provides type info
    propagated as Integer                   Note: Boolean: 1 if propagated, 0 if source
    block_ptr as Integer                    Note: Block containing source
End Type

Note: ============================================================
Note: CONTEXT MANAGEMENT
Note: ============================================================

@Implementation
Creates and initializes a DevirtualizationContext structure for a given CFG.
All counters start at zero, caches are initialized as empty collections,
and thresholds are set to safe defaults.

Memory allocation:
- Context structure: 104 bytes
- virtual_call_sites: List structure
- type_info_map: Dictionary structure
- receiver_types: Dictionary structure
- single_impl_cache: Dictionary structure

Returns pointer to initialized context, or 0 on allocation failure.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_devirtualization_context" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If cfg_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let context_size be 104
    Let context be proc allocate from Layout with context_size

    If context equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Store CFG pointer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 0, cfg_ptr

    Note: Initialize SSA pointer
    Let ssa_ptr be 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, ssa_ptr

    Note: Initialize dominance pointer
    Let dominance_ptr be 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 16, dominance_ptr

    Note: Initialize current_function_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 24, 0

    Note: Initialize counters
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 32, 0  Note: devirtualized_calls
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 40, 0  Note: speculative_devirt
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 48, 0  Note: total_virtual_calls

    Note: Create virtual call sites list
    Let sites be proc create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 56, sites

    Note: Create type info map
    Let type_map be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 64, type_map

    Note: Create receiver types map
    Let receiver_map be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 72, receiver_map

    Note: Initialize blocks_processed counter
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 80, 0

    Note: Create single implementation cache
    Let impl_cache be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 88, impl_cache

    Note: Set guard threshold (75% confidence required for speculative devirt)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 96, 75

    Return context
End Process

@Implementation
Destroys a DevirtualizationContext and frees all associated memory.
This includes freeing all virtual call site structures, type info structures,
caches, and the context itself.

Proper cleanup prevents memory leaks in the optimization pipeline.
@End Implementation

Process called "destroy_devirtualization_context" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Nothing:
    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Free virtual call sites list (including individual structures)
    Let sites be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 56
    If sites is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc length from List with sites
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let site_ptr be proc get from List with sites and i
            If site_ptr is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with site_ptr
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc destroy from List with sites
    End If

    Note: Free type info map
    Let type_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 64
    If type_map is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy from Dictionary with type_map
    End If

    Note: Free receiver types map
    Let receiver_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 72
    If receiver_map is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy from Dictionary with receiver_map
    End If

    Note: Free single implementation cache
    Let impl_cache be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 88
    If impl_cache is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy from Dictionary with impl_cache
    End If

    Note: Free dominance pointer if allocated
    Let dominance_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 16
    If dominance_ptr is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy_dominance_tree from Dominance with dominance_ptr
    End If

    Note: Free context structure
    proc deallocate from Layout with context_ptr
End Process

@Implementation
Prints statistics about devirtualization optimization transformations.
This provides visibility into the effectiveness of the devirtualization pass.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_devirtualization_stats" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Nothing:
    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return
    End If

    Display "========== Devirtualization Statistics =========="

    Let devirt_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 32
    Display "Direct devirtualizations: " joined with devirt_count

    Let spec_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 40
    Display "Speculative devirtualizations: " joined with spec_count

    Let total_virtual be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 48
    Display "Total virtual calls found: " joined with total_virtual

    Let blocks_processed be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 80
    Display "Basic blocks analyzed: " joined with blocks_processed

    Display "================================================="
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: TYPE PROPAGATION ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
Type propagation determines the concrete type of SSA values by tracking
type information through the program.

Type sources:
1. Allocations (NEW instruction) - 100% confidence
2. Type casts (CAST instruction) - 90% confidence
3. Type guards (TYPECHECK instruction) - 85% confidence
4. Function parameters - analyze call sites
5. Phi nodes - merge type information

Propagation:
- Forward through dominators
- Track through assignments
- Merge at phi nodes (minimum confidence)

This enables identifying receiver types for virtual calls.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Analyzes allocation and cast instructions to build initial type information.

Algorithm:
1. Iterate through all blocks in dominator tree order
2. For each instruction:
   - NEW: Record allocation type (100% confidence)
   - CAST: Record target type (90% confidence)
   - TYPECHECK: Record checked type (85% confidence)
3. Create TypePropagationInfo for each typed value
4. Add to type_info_map

Returns number of values with type information collected.
@End Implementation

Process called "collect_type_information" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 0
    If cfg_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let type_info_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 64
    Let type_count be 0

    Note: Get all blocks from CFG
    Let blocks be proc get_all_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let block_idx be 0

    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be proc get from List with blocks and block_idx

        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Note: Get instructions in this block
            Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from CFG with block_ptr
            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
                Let inst_idx be 0

                While inst_idx is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst_ptr be proc get from List with instructions and inst_idx

                    If inst_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be proc get_opcode from MIR with inst_ptr

                        Note: Check for allocation (MIR_NEW = 20400)
                        If opcode equals 20400:
                            Note: Get result value ID
                            Let value_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 8

                            Note: Get allocated type (operand 0)
                            Let type_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 16

                            If value_id is not equal to 0 and type_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                Note: Create TypePropagationInfo
                                Let info_size be 48
                                Let info_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with info_size

                                If info_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 0, value_id
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 8, type_ptr
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 16, 100  Note: 100% confidence
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 24, inst_ptr
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 32, 0  Note: Not propagated
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 40, block_ptr

                                    proc set from Dictionary with type_info_map, value_id, and info_ptr
                                    Set type_count to type_count plus 1
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If

                        Note: Check for type cast (MIR_CAST = 20401)
                        If opcode equals 20401:
                            Set value_id to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 8
                            Let target_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 24

                            If value_id is not equal to 0 and target_type is not equal to 0:
                                Set info_size to 48
                                Set info_ptr to proc allocate from Layout with info_size

                                If info_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 0, value_id
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 8, target_type
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 16, 90  Note: 90% confidence
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 24, inst_ptr
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 32, 0
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 40, block_ptr

                                    proc set from Dictionary with type_info_map, value_id, and info_ptr
                                    Set type_count to type_count plus 1
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If

                        Note: Check for type check (MIR_TYPECHECK = 20402)
                        If opcode equals 20402:
                            Set value_id to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 8
                            Let checked_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 24

                            If value_id is not equal to 0 and checked_type is not equal to 0:
                                Set info_size to 48
                                Set info_ptr to proc allocate from Layout with info_size

                                If info_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 0, value_id
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 8, checked_type
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 16, 85  Note: 85% confidence
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 24, inst_ptr
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 32, 0
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with info_ptr, 40, block_ptr

                                    proc set from Dictionary with type_info_map, value_id, and info_ptr
                                    Set type_count to type_count plus 1
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Set inst_idx to inst_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If

            Note: Update blocks_processed counter
            Let blocks_processed be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 80
            Set blocks_processed to blocks_processed plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 80, blocks_processed
        End If

        Set block_idx to block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return type_count
End Process

@Implementation
Propagates type information through SSA use-def chains.

Algorithm:
1. For each value with type information
2. Find all uses of that value
3. If use is an assignment (MOV), propagate type to destination
4. Lower confidence by 5% at each propagation step
5. Continue until no more propagations possible

This enables tracking types through assignments.

Returns number of propagations performed.
@End Implementation

Process called "propagate_type_information" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let type_info_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 64
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 0
    Let ssa_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8
    Let propagation_count be 0

    Note: Iterative propagation until fixed point
    Let changed be 1
    Let iteration be 0
    Let max_iterations be 20  Note: Prevent infinite loops

    While changed equals 1 and iteration is less than max_iterations:
        Set changed to 0
        Set iteration to iteration plus 1

        Note: Get all blocks in CFG
        Let blocks_ptr be proc get_all_blocks from CFG with cfg
        Let block_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with blocks_ptr, 0
        Let block_idx be 0

        While block_idx is less than block_count:
            Let block_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with blocks_ptr plus 8 plus (block_idx multiplied by 8), 0

            Note: Get block instructions
            Let insts_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block_ptr, 16
            Let inst_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block_ptr, 24
            Let inst_idx be 0

            While inst_idx is less than inst_count:
                Let inst_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with insts_ptr plus (inst_idx multiplied by 8), 0
                Let opcode be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 0

                Note: Check for MOV instruction (20000)
                If opcode equals 20000:
                    Note: Get source and destination
                    Let dest_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 8
                    Let src_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 16

                    Note: Check if source has type information
                    Let src_type_info_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_info_map plus (src_value multiplied by 8), 0

                    If src_type_info_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        Note: Get source type details
                        Let src_type_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with src_type_info_ptr, 8
                        Let src_confidence be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with src_type_info_ptr, 16

                        Note: Check if destination already has type information
                        Let dest_type_info_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_info_map plus (dest_value multiplied by 8), 0

                        If dest_type_info_ptr equals 0:
                            Note: Create new type information for destination
                            Let new_type_info be proc allocate from Layout with 48

                            Note: Copy type but reduce confidence by 5%
                            Let new_confidence be src_confidence minus 5
                            If new_confidence is less than 0:
                                Set new_confidence to 0
                            End If

                            Note: Set fields
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_type_info, 0, dest_value
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_type_info, 8, src_type_ptr
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_type_info, 16, new_confidence
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_type_info, 24, inst_ptr
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_type_info, 32, 1  Note: propagated flag
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with new_type_info, 40, block_ptr

                            Note: Add to type_info_map
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_info_map, (dest_value multiplied by 8), new_type_info

                            Set changed to 1
                            Set propagation_count to propagation_count plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If

                Note: Check for PHI instruction (20001)
                If opcode equals 20001:
                    Note: Get phi destination
                    Let phi_dest be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 8

                    Note: Get phi operands
                    Let phi_op_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 24
                    Let phi_ops_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 32

                    Note: Find common type among all operands
                    Let common_type_ptr be 0
                    Let min_confidence be 100
                    Let all_same_type be 1
                    Let op_idx be 0

                    While op_idx is less than phi_op_count:
                        Let op_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with phi_ops_ptr plus (op_idx multiplied by 16), 0
                        Let op_type_info_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_info_map plus (op_value multiplied by 8), 0

                        If op_type_info_ptr is not equal to 0:
                            Let op_type_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with op_type_info_ptr, 8
                            Let op_confidence be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with op_type_info_ptr, 16

                            If common_type_ptr equals 0:
                                Set common_type_ptr to op_type_ptr
                                Set min_confidence to op_confidence
                            Otherwise:
                                If op_type_ptr is not equal to common_type_ptr:
                                    Set all_same_type to 0  Note: Different types
                                End If
                                If op_confidence is less than min_confidence:
                                    Set min_confidence to op_confidence
                                End If
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            Set all_same_type to 0  Note: Unknown type
                        End If

                        Set op_idx to op_idx plus 1
                    End While

                    Note: If all operands have same type, propagate to phi result
                    If all_same_type equals 1 and common_type_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        Let phi_type_info_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_info_map plus (phi_dest multiplied by 8), 0

                        If phi_type_info_ptr equals 0:
                            Note: Create type information for phi
                            Let phi_type_info be proc allocate from Layout with 48

                            Note: Use minimum confidence - 10% (phi uncertainty)
                            Let phi_confidence be min_confidence minus 10
                            If phi_confidence is less than 0:
                                Set phi_confidence to 0
                            End If

                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_type_info, 0, phi_dest
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_type_info, 8, common_type_ptr
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_type_info, 16, phi_confidence
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_type_info, 24, inst_ptr
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_type_info, 32, 1
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_type_info, 40, block_ptr

                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with type_info_map, (phi_dest multiplied by 8), phi_type_info

                            Set changed to 1
                            Set propagation_count to propagation_count plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If

                Set inst_idx to inst_idx plus 1
            End While

            Set block_idx to block_idx plus 1
        End While
    End While

    Return propagation_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: VIRTUAL CALL ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
Virtual call analysis identifies indirect calls through vtables and
determines if we have enough type information to devirtualize them.

Virtual calls in MIR:
- MIR_CALL_INDIRECT with protocol/trait receiver
- Receiver value must have type information
- Method selector identifies which method to resolve

We analyze each virtual call to determine:
1. Receiver type (concrete or unknown)
2. Method implementation for that type
3. Confidence level for devirtualization
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Scans all basic blocks and identifies virtual call instructions.

Algorithm:
1. Iterate through all basic blocks
2. Examine all instructions looking for MIR_CALL_INDIRECT
3. Extract receiver value ID and method selector
4. Query type information for receiver
5. Create VirtualCallSite structure
6. Add to virtual_call_sites list

Returns number of virtual call sites found.
@End Implementation

Process called "collect_virtual_call_sites" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 0
    If cfg_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let virtual_sites be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 56
    Let type_info_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 64
    Let site_count be 0

    Note: Get all blocks from CFG
    Let blocks be proc get_all_blocks from CFG with cfg_ptr
    If blocks equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let block_idx be 0

    While block_idx is less than block_count:
        Let block_ptr be proc get from List with blocks and block_idx

        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Note: Get instructions in this block
            Let instructions be proc get_block_instructions from CFG with block_ptr
            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
                Let inst_idx be 0

                While inst_idx is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst_ptr be proc get from List with instructions and inst_idx

                    If inst_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        Let opcode be proc get_opcode from MIR with inst_ptr

                        Note: Check for indirect call (MIR_CALL_INDIRECT = 20305)
                        If opcode equals 20305:
                            Note: Get receiver value ID (operand 0)
                            Let receiver_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 16

                            Note: Get method selector (operand 1)
                            Let method_selector be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst_ptr, 24

                            If receiver_id is not equal to 0:
                                Note: Query type information for receiver
                                Let type_info be proc get from Dictionary with type_info_map and receiver_id

                                Let concrete_type be 0
                                Let confidence be 0

                                If type_info is not equal to 0:
                                    Set concrete_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_info, 8
                                    Set confidence to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with type_info, 16
                                End If

                                Note: Create VirtualCallSite structure
                                Let site_size be 72
                                Let site_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with site_size

                                If site_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 0, inst_ptr
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 8, block_ptr
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 16, receiver_id
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 24, method_selector
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 32, 0  Note: protocol_ptr
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 40, concrete_type
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 48, confidence

                                    Note: Can devirtualize if confidence high enough
                                    Let can_devirt be 0
                                    If confidence is greater than or equal to 75:
                                        Set can_devirt to 1
                                    End If
                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 56, can_devirt

                                    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 64, 0  Note: Not devirtualized yet

                                    proc append from List with virtual_sites and site_ptr
                                    Set site_count to site_count plus 1
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Set inst_idx to inst_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If

        Set block_idx to block_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update total_virtual_calls counter
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 48, site_count

    Return site_count
End Process

@Implementation
Resolves the concrete implementation of a method for a given type.

Algorithm:
1. Look up type's method table
2. Find method implementation for selector
3. Verify method is callable
4. Return function pointer to implementation

Returns function pointer to implementation, or 0 if not found.
@End Implementation

Process called "resolve_method_implementation" that takes concrete_type as Integer, method_selector as Integer, context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If concrete_type equals 0 or method_selector equals 0 or context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get type's vtable (offset 64 in type structure)
    Let vtable_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with concrete_type, 64
    If vtable_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Vtable structure:
    Note: Offset 0: entry count (Integer)
    Note: Offset 8: entries array (each entry 16 bytes: selector + function_ptr)

    Let entry_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with vtable_ptr, 0
    Let entries_ptr be vtable_ptr plus 8

    Note: Linear search through vtable entries
    Let entry_idx be 0
    While entry_idx is less than entry_count:
        Let entry_offset be entry_idx multiplied by 16
        Let entry_selector be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entries_ptr plus entry_offset plus 0, 0
        Let entry_function be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entries_ptr plus entry_offset plus 8, 0

        Note: Check if selector matches
        If entry_selector equals method_selector:
            Note: Verify function pointer is valid
            If entry_function is not equal to 0:
                Return entry_function
            End If
        End If

        Set entry_idx to entry_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Method not found in vtable - check single implementation cache
    Let single_impl_cache be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 88
    Let cached_impl be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with single_impl_cache plus (method_selector multiplied by 8), 0
    If cached_impl is not equal to 0:
        Return cached_impl
    End If

    Note: Try to resolve from type's protocol/trait information
    Note: Type structure offset 72: protocol list pointer
    Let protocol_list_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with concrete_type, 72
    If protocol_list_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Note: Search protocols for method implementation
        Let protocol_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with protocol_list_ptr, 0
        Let protocols_ptr be protocol_list_ptr plus 8
        Let protocol_idx be 0

        While protocol_idx is less than protocol_count:
            Let protocol_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with protocols_ptr plus (protocol_idx multiplied by 8), 0

            Note: Get protocol's method table
            Let protocol_vtable_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with protocol_ptr, 64
            If protocol_vtable_ptr is not equal to 0:
                Let protocol_entry_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with protocol_vtable_ptr, 0
                Let protocol_entries_ptr be protocol_vtable_ptr plus 8
                Let protocol_entry_idx be 0

                While protocol_entry_idx is less than protocol_entry_count:
                    Let pentry_offset be protocol_entry_idx multiplied by 16
                    Let pentry_selector be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with protocol_entries_ptr plus pentry_offset plus 0, 0
                    Let pentry_function be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with protocol_entries_ptr plus pentry_offset plus 8, 0

                    If pentry_selector equals method_selector:
                        If pentry_function is not equal to 0:
                            Note: Cache for future lookups
                            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with single_impl_cache, (method_selector multiplied by 8), pentry_function
                            Return pentry_function
                        End If
                    End If

                    Set protocol_entry_idx to protocol_entry_idx plus 1
                End While
            End If

            Set protocol_idx to protocol_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Method not found
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: DEVIRTUALIZATION TRANSFORMATION
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
Devirtualization transformation converts virtual calls into direct calls.

Two strategies:
1. Direct devirtualization: Known concrete type → replace with direct call
2. Speculative devirtualization: Likely type → add type guard + fast path

Direct devirtualization:
- Simple replacement of CALL_INDIRECT with CALL
- No control flow changes
- Only when confidence = 100%

Speculative devirtualization:
- Insert type guard before call
- Split block: fast path (direct) vs slow path (virtual)
- Merge results with phi node
- Used when confidence > or equal to threshold (75%)
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Performs direct devirtualization transformation.

Algorithm:
1. Get concrete implementation for receiver type
2. Replace MIR_CALL_INDIRECT with MIR_CALL
3. Update callee to point to concrete implementation
4. Update SSA use-def chains

Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure.
@End Implementation

Process called "perform_direct_devirtualization" that takes site_ptr as Integer, context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If site_ptr equals 0 or context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get call instruction and concrete type
    Let call_inst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 0
    Let concrete_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 40
    Let method_selector be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 24

    If call_inst equals 0 or concrete_type equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Resolve method implementation
    Let impl_ptr be resolve_method_implementation(concrete_type, method_selector, context_ptr)
    If impl_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Replace CALL_INDIRECT (20305) with CALL (20304)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with call_inst, 0, 20304

    Note: Set callee to concrete implementation (operand 0)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with call_inst, 16, impl_ptr

    Note: Mark as devirtualized
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 64, 1

    Return 1
End Process

@Implementation
Performs speculative devirtualization transformation with type guard.

Algorithm:
1. Get likely concrete implementation
2. Split call block before call instruction
3. Insert type guard checking receiver type
4. Create fast path (direct call) and slow path (virtual call)
5. Merge paths with phi node for result

Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure.
@End Implementation

Process called "perform_speculative_devirtualization" that takes site_ptr as Integer, context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If site_ptr equals 0 or context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get call information
    Let call_inst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 0
    Let call_block be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 8
    Let receiver_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 16
    Let method_selector be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 24
    Let concrete_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 40
    Let confidence be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 48

    If call_inst equals 0 or concrete_type equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check confidence threshold
    Let threshold be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 96
    If confidence is less than threshold:
        Return 0  Note: Not confident enough
    End If

    Note: Resolve concrete implementation
    Let impl_ptr be resolve_method_implementation(concrete_type, method_selector, context_ptr)
    If impl_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get CFG for block manipulation
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 0

    Note: Create type guard block
    Let guard_block be proc create_basic_block from CFG with cfg
    If guard_block equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create fast path block (direct call)
    Let fast_path_block be proc create_basic_block from CFG with cfg
    If fast_path_block equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create slow path block (virtual call)
    Let slow_path_block be proc create_basic_block from CFG with cfg
    If slow_path_block equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create merge block
    Let merge_block be proc create_basic_block from CFG with cfg
    If merge_block equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find call instruction index in call block
    Let call_block_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_block, 16
    Let inst_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_block, 24
    Let call_inst_idx be 0
    Let found_call be 0

    While call_inst_idx is less than inst_count:
        Let current_inst be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_block_insts plus (call_inst_idx multiplied by 8), 0
        If current_inst equals call_inst:
            Set found_call to 1
            Break
        End If
        Set call_inst_idx to call_inst_idx plus 1
    End While

    If found_call equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Move instructions after call to merge block
    Let move_idx be call_inst_idx plus 1
    While move_idx is less than inst_count:
        Let inst_to_move be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_block_insts plus (move_idx multiplied by 8), 0
        proc add_instruction_to_block from CFG with merge_block, inst_to_move
        Set move_idx to move_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Truncate call block at call (guard will be added)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with call_block, 24, call_inst_idx

    Note: Build type guard: TYPECHECK receiver against concrete_type
    Let guard_inst be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with guard_inst, 0, 20402  Note: MIR_TYPECHECK
    Let guard_result be receiver_id plus 5000000  Note: Unique value ID for guard result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with guard_inst, 8, guard_result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with guard_inst, 16, receiver_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with guard_inst, 24, concrete_type
    proc add_instruction_to_block from CFG with guard_block, guard_inst

    Note: Add conditional branch on guard result
    Let guard_branch be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with guard_branch, 0, 20302  Note: MIR_BR (conditional branch)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with guard_branch, 8, guard_result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with guard_branch, 16, fast_path_block
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with guard_branch, 24, slow_path_block
    proc add_instruction_to_block from CFG with guard_block, guard_branch

    Note: Wire call block -> guard block
    proc add_edge from CFG with call_block, guard_block

    Note: Build fast path: direct call to concrete implementation
    Let fast_call be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with fast_call, 0, 20304  Note: MIR_CALL (direct)
    Let fast_result be receiver_id plus 6000000  Note: Unique value ID for fast result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with fast_call, 8, fast_result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with fast_call, 16, impl_ptr

    Note: Copy arguments from original call
    Let arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_inst, 24
    Let args_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_inst, 32
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with fast_call, 24, arg_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with fast_call, 32, args_ptr
    proc add_instruction_to_block from CFG with fast_path_block, fast_call

    Note: Jump from fast path to merge
    Let fast_jump be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with fast_jump, 0, 20301  Note: MIR_JMP
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with fast_jump, 8, merge_block
    proc add_instruction_to_block from CFG with fast_path_block, fast_jump
    proc add_edge from CFG with fast_path_block, merge_block

    Note: Build slow path: keep original virtual call
    Let slow_call be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with slow_call, 0, 20305  Note: MIR_CALL_INDIRECT (virtual)
    Let slow_result be receiver_id plus 7000000  Note: Unique value ID for slow result

    Note: Copy all fields from original call
    Let call_opcode be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_inst, 0
    Let call_result be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_inst, 8
    Let call_target be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_inst, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with slow_call, 8, slow_result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with slow_call, 16, call_target
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with slow_call, 24, arg_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with slow_call, 32, args_ptr
    proc add_instruction_to_block from CFG with slow_path_block, slow_call

    Note: Jump from slow path to merge
    Let slow_jump be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with slow_jump, 0, 20301  Note: MIR_JMP
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with slow_jump, 8, merge_block
    proc add_instruction_to_block from CFG with slow_path_block, slow_jump
    proc add_edge from CFG with slow_path_block, merge_block

    Note: Build phi node in merge block to select result
    Let phi_inst be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_inst, 0, 20001  Note: MIR_PHI
    Let call_result_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with call_inst, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_inst, 8, call_result_id  Note: Use original result ID
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_inst, 16, 2  Note: Two operands

    Note: Build phi operands array: [fast_result, fast_path_block, slow_result, slow_path_block]
    Let phi_ops be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_ops, 0, fast_result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_ops, 8, fast_path_block
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_ops, 16, slow_result
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_ops, 24, slow_path_block
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_inst, 24, 2
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with phi_inst, 32, phi_ops
    proc add_instruction_to_block from CFG with merge_block, phi_inst

    Note: Add all new blocks to CFG
    proc add_block_to_function from CFG with cfg, guard_block
    proc add_block_to_function from CFG with cfg, fast_path_block
    proc add_block_to_function from CFG with cfg, slow_path_block
    proc add_block_to_function from CFG with cfg, merge_block

    Note: Update SSA form
    Let ssa_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 8
    If ssa_ptr is not equal to 0:
        proc recompute_ssa from SSA with cfg, ssa_ptr
    End If

    Note: Mark as devirtualized (speculative)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 64, 1

    Note: Increment speculative counter
    Let speculative_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 40, (speculative_count plus 1)

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: MAIN ENTRY POINTS
Note: ============================================================

@Implementation
Main entry point for devirtualization optimization.

Algorithm:
1. Create context
2. Collect type information
3. Propagate type information
4. Collect virtual call sites
5. Perform direct devirtualization
6. Perform speculative devirtualization
7. Print statistics
8. Clean up

Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure.
@End Implementation

Process called "optimize_function_with_devirtualization" that takes function_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If function_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Display "Starting devirtualization optimization"

    Note: Get CFG from function
    Let cfg_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with function_ptr, 8
    If cfg_ptr equals 0:
        Display "Function has no CFG, skipping devirtualization"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create context
    Let context_ptr be create_devirtualization_context(cfg_ptr)
    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Display "Failed to create devirtualization context"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Set current function
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 24, function_ptr

    Note: Collect type information
    Let type_count be collect_type_information(context_ptr)
    Display "Collected type information for " joined with type_count joined with " values"

    Note: Propagate type information
    Let prop_count be propagate_type_information(context_ptr)
    Display "Propagated " joined with prop_count joined with " type assignments"

    Note: Collect virtual call sites
    Let virtual_count be collect_virtual_call_sites(context_ptr)
    Display "Found " joined with virtual_count joined with " virtual call sites"

    If virtual_count equals 0:
        Display "No virtual calls found, skipping devirtualization"
        destroy_devirtualization_context(context_ptr)
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Devirtualize calls
    Let sites be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 56
    Let direct_count be 0
    Let spec_count be 0
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than virtual_count:
        Let site_ptr be proc get from List with sites and i

        If site_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let can_devirt be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 56
            Let confidence be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with site_ptr, 48

            If can_devirt equals 1:
                Note: Try direct devirtualization for 100% confidence
                If confidence equals 100:
                    Let success be perform_direct_devirtualization(site_ptr, context_ptr)
                    If success equals 1:
                        Set direct_count to direct_count plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                    Note: Try speculative devirtualization for high confidence
                    Set success to perform_speculative_devirtualization(site_ptr, context_ptr)
                    If success equals 1:
                        Set spec_count to spec_count plus 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update statistics
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 32, direct_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context_ptr, 40, spec_count

    Note: Print statistics
    print_devirtualization_stats(context_ptr)

    Note: Clean up
    destroy_devirtualization_context(context_ptr)

    Display "Devirtualization optimization complete"

    Return 1
End Process

@Implementation
Entry point for running devirtualization pass on entire program.

Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure.
@End Implementation

Process called "run_devirtualization_pass" that takes program_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If program_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get all functions
    Let functions be proc get_program_functions from MIR with program_ptr
    If functions equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let func_count be proc length from List with functions
    Let optimized_count be 0
    Let i be 0

    Display "Running devirtualization pass on " joined with func_count joined with " functions"

    While i is less than func_count:
        Let func_ptr be proc get from List with functions and i

        If func_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let is_external be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with func_ptr, 80
            If is_external equals 0:
                Let success be optimize_function_with_devirtualization(func_ptr)
                If success equals 1:
                    Set optimized_count to optimized_count plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Display "Devirtualization completed for " joined with optimized_count joined with " functions"

    Return 1
End Process

@Implementation
Profitability check for devirtualization optimization.

Devirtualization is beneficial when:
1. Function contains indirect calls (has opportunities)
2. Optimization level > or equal to 2 (devirt at -O2 and above)
3. Not a tiny function (overhead not worth it)

Returns 1 if should run, 0 otherwise.
@End Implementation

Process called "should_run_devirtualization" that takes function_ptr as Integer, optimization_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Devirtualization at -O2 and above
    If optimization_level is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if function has indirect calls
    If function_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Let indirect_count be proc count_instructions_of_type from MIR with function_ptr, 20305
        If indirect_count is greater than 0:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: PASS METADATA
Note: ============================================================

@Implementation
Returns the name of this optimization pass.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_devirtualization_pass_name" that takes nothing returns Integer:
    Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Devirtualization"
End Process

@Implementation
Returns a description of this optimization pass.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_devirtualization_pass_description" that takes nothing returns Integer:
    Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Converts virtual calls to direct calls using type propagation analysis to eliminate indirect call overhead"
End Process
